HTML stands for hyper text markup language. Here hyper text means text which can do more than a normal text, it can be used for styling, creating link, making borders etc. in a webpage. Markup language means language that can give structure to webpage. So, HTML is a language which gives content and structure to the webpages.
HTML is considered the backbone of webpage as it gives structure to the webpages.
HTML can be used for making websites for businesses, educational purposes, charity purposes etc.
HTML is used to give contents and structure to webpages. It is of static nature and it doesn't changes its function unless html code writer changes something in the code. Whereas a programming language is of dynamic nature. It gives computer some instructions to process and give output. Its output can vary according to the input.
